Coloring Anyone

Easy to learn, easy to do!

May 17, 2021 • Silva, Lincon • 1 min read

people   photos   black_white

Are we going to learn how to use some python libraries?

In this example, we will learn how to color photos, just to show how much we can do using python. Let's go?

Let's go to learn?

Loading a library that can help you is the first step on this path, I am using the deoldify_wrapper.py library.

#hide_output
! wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/awarischool/data-science/master/image-colorizer/deoldify_wrapper.py

Second step is import de Deoldify method from deoldify_wrapper

#hide_output
from deoldify_wrapper import DeOldify

Now, let's instantiate the imported class

#hide_output
deoldify = DeOldify()

At this time we send the photo and the input method parameters to color the photo.

deoldify.colorize("https://www.awebic.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/pexels-dishan-lathiya-872756.jpg", render_factor=10)
